    "game-obj": "Feats",
    "feat": {
        "name": "Hedge Maze",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "subtype": "feat",
        "text": "You sculpt a manicured maze of hedges. Up to 10 hedges spring from the ground where you choose in a 30-foot-square area within 120 feet. Each is 10 feet long, 5 feet wide, and 15 feet tall. The hedges grant standard cover, are difficult terrain, and have a Climb DC of 15. They last until the end of your next turn, and you can Sustain the impulse up to 1 minute  \n  \n You can spend 10 minutes using this impulse as an exploration activity to instead create a *cozy cabin* with hedges for walls. It lasts for 12 hours, but ends if you use the impulse again.",
        "level": 12,
        "action_type": {
            "type": "stat_block_section",
            "subtype": "action_type",
            "name": "Three Actions"
        },
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Impulse",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Rage of Elements",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Rage of Elements pg. 15",
                            "alt": "Rage of Elements pg. 15",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        },
                        "page": 15,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "f83779b12b3f1e7096ae9a32ca68ea4f",
                "text": "The primary magical actions kineticists use are called impulses. You can use an impulse only if your kinetic aura is active and channeling that element, and only if you have a hand free to shape the elemental flow. The impulse trait means the action has the concentrate trait unless another ability changes this. If an impulse allows you to choose an element, you can choose any element you're channeling, and the impulse gains that element's trait.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "concentrate",
                        "alt": "concentrate",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Kineticist",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Rage of Elements",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Rage of Elements pg. 237",
                            "alt": "Rage of Elements pg. 237",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        },
                        "page": 237,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "721afce0c1e219e9edd3709db105bb4e",
                "text": "This indicates abilities from the kineticist class.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "kineticist",
                        "alt": "kineticist",
                        "game-obj": "Classes",
                        "aonid": 23
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Manipulate",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 104,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 458,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "6a0bf3cdfe7c0fc427c7b8ea9310f113",
                "text": "You must physically manipulate an item or make gestures to use an action with this trait. Creatures without a suitable appendage can\u2019t perform actions with this trait. Manipulate actions often trigger reactions."
            },
            {
                "name": "Overflow",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Rage of Elements",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Rage of Elements pg. 15",
                            "alt": "Rage of Elements pg. 15",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        },
                        "page": 15,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "ad03e04f8b701bd9c018b87e35173733",
                "text": "Powerful impulses temporarily overdraw the energy of your kinetic gate. When you use an impulse that has the overflow trait, your kinetic aura deactivates until you revitalize it (typically with Channel Elements). Extinguishing your element this severely is taxing, and consequently, you can use only one overflow impulse per round, even if you reactivate your kinetic gate.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Channel Elements",
                        "alt": "Channel Elements",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 2124
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Plant",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 125,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 459",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 459",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 459,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "651e06f09e5aea780d7c70a36ce5b1f2",
                "text": "Vegetable creatures have the plant trait. They are distinct from normal plants. Magical effects with this trait manipulate or conjure plants or plant matter in some way. Effects that manipulate plants have no effect in an area with no plants."
            },
            {
                "name": "Primal",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 134,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 460",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 460",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 460,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "60a4f011afd1e0fac8211bd01108d104",
                "text": "This magic comes from the primal tradition, connecting to the natural world and instinct. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to primal magic."
            },
            {
                "name": "Wood",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 463",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 463",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 463,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "7c548a9e0a2647c082989720b3de0a87",
                "text": "Effects with the wood trait conjure or manipulate wood. Those that manipulate wood have no effect in an area without wood. Creatures with this trait consist primarily of wood or have a connection to magical wood.  \n  \nThese planes consist of trees and other flora latticed in organic patterns. Wood planes are often perfectly constructed to match their desired purpose or environment but aren\u2019t usually outright hostile to visitors."
            }
        ],
